{"word":"ἔφημαι","slug":"ἔφημαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔφημαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> used as a <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <a href='S:ἧμαι'><el>ἧμαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be set</i> or <i>seated on, to sit on</i>, <el>θρόνῳ</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>θινὸς ἐφήμενος</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:— <i>to be seated at</i> or <i>in</i>, <el>δόμοις</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: —also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>βρέτας ἐφήμενος</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>  <div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to act as assessor</i> (<a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>ἔφεδρος</el>), <el>Παλλὰς οἵ τ' ἐφήμενοι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}